         <signavio:signavioDiagramMetaData metaKey="meta-processdescription" metaValue="This activity is usually outsource to other financial institutions then underwriters on using international and national settlement networks. Usually, two institutions are involved, one for the settlement of securities and one for the settlement of the capital payment in the appropriate accounts.  Usually, there is no delivery of the physical certificate because settlement networks maintain book-based positions."/>
